<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="different-adj">different <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'dɪfrənt/    美 /'dɪfrənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>有差异的；不同的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 similar </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Old English is very <strong>different from</strong> the English we speak nowadays.
古英语与我们今天使用的英语有很大差别。</p><footer>译林③ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-various">2.★ <strong>各种的 (various)；另外的 ：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Different people feel stress <strong>in different ways</strong>.
不同的人对压力有不同的感受。</p><footer>2012 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She resigned and moved to a different job.
她辞了职，改做另一份工作。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>differently /'dɪfrəntli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I enjoyed studying difference kinds of cars and planes. (改错)  （2017 全国）  </li>
<li>The way he did it was different <strong><em>_</em></strong> what we were used to.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. difference → different  2. from  </p></div>